A similar closed form for the action eq:nlnonkahler  cannot be given,
but the explicit derivation of some parts thereof is straightforward on the
same lines. eq:kahlerexp  and eq:suppotexp  together with
eq:kahlercond  and eq:suppotcond  define the invariant part of
the effective action, only. Adding a term generating the correct anomalies terminates the construction of
the effective action.

The Effective Potential 

